DA  - 1995/03/01
TI  - Publishing International Business Research: A Survey of Leading Journals
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 69
EP  - 89
VL  - 26
IS  - 1
AB  - This paper argues that, given the proliferation of journals within which to publish international business research, authors need to identify objectives for their research and develop a publishing strategy to ensure the appropriate and timely publication of their work. Based on archival data and a survey of journal editors, this study provides information about seventy-nine English language business publications to help authors develop such as strategy.
